color-shading-type             : val='solid'      : desc=How to shade the background colour. Possible values are “horizontal”, “vertical”, and “solid”.\n  key= embedded-keyboard-command      : val=''           : desc=The command that will be run, if the “embedded_keyboard_enabled” key is set to TRUE, to embed a keyboard widget into the window. This command should implement an XEMBED plug interface and output a window XID on the standard output.\n\nDEPRECATED: This key is deprecated and ignored.\n  key= embedded-keyboard-enabled      : val=false        : desc=Set this to TRUE to allow embedding a keyboard into the window when trying to unlock. The “keyboard_command” key must be set with the appropriate command.\n\nDEPRECATED: This key is deprecated and ignored.\n  key= idle-activation-enabled        : val=true         : desc=Set this to TRUE to activate the screensaver when the session is idle.\n\nDEPRECATED: This key is deprecated and ignored. Set org.gnome.desktop.session idle-delay to 0 if you do not want to activate the screensaver.\n  key= lock-delay                     : val=uint32 0     : desc=The number of seconds after screensaver activation before locking the screen.\n  key= lock-enabled                   : val=true         : desc=Set this to TRUE to lock the screen when the screensaver goes active.\n  key= logout-command                 : val=''           : desc=The command to invoke when the logout button is clicked. This command should simply log the user out without any interaction. This key has effect only if the “logout_enable” key is set to TRUE.\n\nDEPRECATED: This key is deprecated and ignored.\n  key= logout-delay                   : val=uint32 7200  : desc=The number of seconds after the screensaver activation before a logout option will appear in the unlock dialog. This key has effect only if the “logout_enable” key is set to TRUE.\n\nDEPRECATED: This key is deprecated and ignored\n  key= logout-enabled                 : val=false        : desc=Set this to TRUE to offer an option in the unlock dialog to allow logging out after a delay. The delay is specified in the “logout_delay” key.\n\nDEPRECATED: This key is deprecated and ignored.\n  key= picture-opacity                : val=100          : desc=Opacity with which to draw the background picture.\n  key= picture-options                : val='zoom'       : desc=Determines how the image set by wallpaper_filename is rendered. Possible values are “none”, “wallpaper”, “centered”, “scaled”, “stretched”, “zoom”, “spanned”.\n  key= picture-uri                    : val='file:///usr/share/backgrounds/gnome/adwaita-timed.xml' : desc=URI to use for the background image. Note that the backend only supports local (file://) URIs.\n  key= primary-color                  : val='#023c88'    : desc=Left or Top colour when drawing gradients, or the solid colour.\n  key= secondary-color                : val='#5789ca'    : desc=Right or Bottom colour when drawing gradients, not used for solid colour.\n  key= show-full-name-in-top-bar      : val=true         : desc=Whether the user’s full name is shown in the lock screen or not. This only affects the screen shield, the name is always shown in the unlock dialogue.\n  key= status-message-enabled         : val=true         : desc=Allow the session status message to be displayed when the screen is locked.\n\nDEPRECATED: This key is deprecated and ignored.\n  key= ubuntu-lock-on-suspend         : val=true         : desc=Set this to TRUE to lock the screen when the system suspends.\n  key= user-switch-enabled            : val=true         : desc=Set this to TRUE to offer an option in the unlock dialogue to switch to a different user account.\nUsage:\n  gsettings
